Let us introduce you to <b>Mitch</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Mitch has lived at <a href='/home/?user=msoccer10'>4437-C Mason Circle</a> in Metro Park since September 30, 2007. He describes himself as very Comical. The bright flame colored sunglasses he's wearing may add to any comedic performance he's putting on, or he may just wear them to be stylish. Either way, they're sure to catch your attention.<br><br>Mitch's love for the outdoors shows, and if you're ever over at his place, you might be able to check out all of his camping gear in his sanctuary of freedom. Unless you want to enjoy a view of the stars, you'll probably want to bring your own sleeping bag and tent. <br><br>Speaking of stars, Mitch also has trophies for both Galactic Defender and Countdown. He likes to bring it back down to earth with a little Surfari and Peabody Park Half-Pipe, both of which he also has trophies for. <br><br>If the weather's nice, you could have a barbeque in Mitch's backyard. Delicious food goes great with hanging out by the pool. You could also try to perfect your swan dive off of his Olympic regulation diving board. Remember to wait 30 minutes after eating before you swim to avoid any cramping.<br><br>If you bump into Mitch, be sure to congratulate him and thank him for being such a great Citizen.</div>
